# SpecGate IDE Plugins

SpecGate setup starts with the CLI:

```bash
curl -fsSL "{{.RegistryBaseURL}}/cli/install.sh" | sh
```

Codex and Claude Code can use their plugin managers. Do not combine that method
with CLI-installed files for the same IDE.

The CLI installs or refreshes agent-specific skills and integration files:

```bash
specgate plugins install                 # interactive picker
specgate plugins install --agent all     # cursor|codex|claude|all
```

Add `--dry-run` to preview what would be written without touching disk. Add
`--registry {{.RegistryBaseURL}}` if the CLI is not already configured for this
server. By default, IDE files are installed globally under your home directory.
Add `--project-local` only when the current repository should vendor its
SpecGate agent setup.

Global installs write IDE-specific plugin packages and hooks for Codex and
Claude Code, plus focused skills. Cursor receives focused skills and its rule.
Project-local installs write only the files each IDE discovers from a repository.

The served `/plugins/package.json` file is the package inventory. It declares
the focused Skills and exact files this server will publish under `/plugins/*`.

Human mode lists the IDE files written or removed and ends with the selected
agent list plus the `specgate plugins doctor` follow-up.
Restart the selected IDEs after installation so they pick up the new files.
Refresh removes obsolete SpecGate-owned skill names, rules, and prior versioned
Codex cache bundles; unowned files are preserved.

When a native Codex or Claude Code installation exists, CLI install stops before
writing. CLI update and uninstall touch only CLI-owned files.

Per-IDE default destinations:
- **Cursor**: writes `~/.cursor/rules/using-specgate.mdc` and focused skills to `~/.cursor/skills/`.
- **Codex**: writes the native plugin package, including focused skills and bundled hooks, to `~/.codex/plugins/specgate/`.
- **Claude Code**: writes the native plugin package, including focused skills and bundled hooks, to `~/.claude/skills/specgate/`.

With `--project-local`, each IDE receives the `specgate` root skill and focused
`specgate-*` phase skills:

- Codex: `.agents/skills/specgate` and `.agents/skills/specgate-*`
- Claude Code: `.claude/skills/specgate` and `.claude/skills/specgate-*`
- Cursor: `.cursor/skills/specgate`, `.cursor/skills/specgate-*`, and
  `.cursor/rules/using-specgate.mdc`

Project-local Codex and Claude Code installs do not change plugin marketplace or
IDE configuration files.

## Skill invocation modes

`specgate` selects one narrow phase when the user explicitly mentions
SpecGate. Read-only SpecGate questions stay in the root skill; generic framework or
coding prompts are not claimed by the plugin.

`specgate-project-setup` is explicit setup for initialization, workspace binding,
plugin installation or refresh, and setup diagnosis.

Lifecycle skills stay focused: `specgate-work-preparation` covers quick-work
creation or artifact readiness through human approval;
`specgate-work-delivery` covers approved implementation, criterion evidence,
authoritative status routing, and the human handoff. Only one phase acts at a
time.
